This is merely my own observation, so take it as that, but in the local Toronto newspapers, there seems to be an awful lot of ads lately telling the common man how huge profits can be easily made in real estate (flipping, essentially). Looks fishy to me. Is that some kind of warning that the next leg is down? Not just in the US, but also in Canada?

